[SN]TITLE[SN]
UK extradition of Ukrainian murder and smuggling suspect begins

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Extradition proceedings have begun against a Ukrainian man suspected of murder and allegedly helping a criminal operation smuggle people to the UK.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Marian Shkirko, 33, from Ukraine, was arrested in Battersea in south-west London on Friday in a joint operation with Belgian police.
He is suspected of using complicit drivers and false documentation.
He was remanded in custody at Westminster Magistrates' Court until 5 February.
Belgian police also want to question him over the alleged murder of a Lithuanian lorry driver in Belgium last year.
Mr Shkirko was arrested by National Crime Agency officers using European warrants, in an operation co-ordinated by the UK's Organised Immigration Crime Taskforce.
